briefdescription.para:
IsFabricated refers to when the ParserSession expected a node to be valid, but it wasn't.
For example, a function invocation on an undefined function will construct a BoundFunctionInvocationNode with IsFabricated set to true.

detaileddescription.para: This stores the indices of tokens that deliminate the parameters to the 'base()' invocation. The reason for this is the invocation needs to have 'string firstName' in scope. But, 'string firstName' doesn't come into scope until the '{' token.
So, remember where the parameters to the 'base()' invocation were, then later when 'string firstName' is in scope, parse the parameters.

briefdescription.para: Once the code block owner's scope has been constructed, this method gives them an opportunity to pull any variables into scope that ought to be there. As well, the current code block builder will have been updated.
